fulltitle: The Hang - A Conversation with Archie Shepp
description: January 5, 2014 - Bret Primack and Willard Jenkins - The Hang - A Conversation with Archie Shepp. Archie discusses his new recording - I Hear the Sound, with his Attica Blues Orchestra, his early days in Philly as a teenage musician with Lee Morgan, coming to New York and becoming part of what was then called the Avant Garde, the effect that Albert Ayler had on his music, the infamous Ascension recording session with John Coltrane, getting into education as a teacher at the University of Massachusetts, making France a second home, and the political and culture situation in the US today.
title: The Hang - A Conversation with Archie Shepp
